The Curtiss R3C was a single-engine biplane from the competition created by the american company, Curtiss Aeroplane and Motor Company in 1925 in order to win the speed record for aircraft of its category.
TecnicaL'R3C was an aircraft from the appearance of the conventional for the era, single-engine biplane, single-seater made in legnoThe Curtiss R3C Racer in Holcomb's Aerodrome., both configuration and terrestrial, designated C-1, seaplane, designated C-2.The fuselage was characterized by the monocoque structure made of wood and from the passenger compartment open. Rear ended in a fin traditional monoderiva characterized by the adoption of a horizontal plane mounted cantilever.The configuration the wingspan was biplane-sesquiplana, with the lower wing, mounted low, smaller than the upper, is mounted high, and is connected by a pair of uprights supplemented by tie rods in steel wire.Depending on the version, the lower part of the fuselage was connected, by a castle tubular, or a trolley-bicyclo traditional, fixed, integrated in the rear by a shoe on the support, or a couple of floats in the hydro version.The propulsion was entrusted to an engine Curtiss V-1400 positioned on the muzzle, a twelve-cylinder V, capable of delivering a power of 619 hp (462 kW).
